18:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Copysmith and GrowthBar share a solid foundation of core features including Short Form, Templates, Team Collaboration. Where Copysmith pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Tone Control and Multilingual and Api Access, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, GrowthBar uniquely offers Long Form and Seo Tools and Browser Extension, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Copysmith holds an overall score of 6/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while GrowthBar scores 6/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
19:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Copysmith offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $19/mo, compared to GrowthBar's starting price of $36/mo. Copysmith has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. GrowthBar does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
